<concept id="concept_6C79964B4EA9478D8569760F6D1E9DB4"> 
  <title>Asset File Requirements for Sharing</title> 
  <shortdesc>Allowed file types and size limitations for sharing assets between
	 the Marketing Cloud and Creative Cloud.
  </shortdesc> 
  <prolog> 
	 <metadata> 
		<keywords> 
		  <keyword>asset sharing</keyword> 
		  <keyword>Creative Cloud</keyword> 
		</keywords> 
		<othermeta name="solution" content="Marketing Cloud"/> </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <conbody>
	 <section id="section_52B6A40BB00B45BC944C01C49B4BB590"> 
		<title>File Types Allowed for Upload</title> 
		<p>File types you can upload include most images, documents, and
		  multimedia. See 
		  <xref
			href="http://docs.adobe.com/docs/en/marketing-cloud/assets/supported-formats.html"
			format="http" scope="external">Supported Formats</xref> for information about
		  file formats in 
		  <keyword>Marketing Cloud</keyword> Assets. 
		</p> 
	 </section> 
	 <section id="section_410ED8E24DBD4136830AE679C6B10D88"> 
		<title>File Size Limitations</title> 
		<p> File size limitations come from the browser and can vary from browser
		  to browser: 
		</p> 
